lipsia (2.1.4)

  * vdotrans3d is now capable of taking 2 transforms. This allows a new approach of normalizing using an anatomical image.
  * adatped code to the new isis (0.4.0) api
  * vmovcorrection and vslicetime now using omp
  * added colin atlas to /usr/share/lipsia
  * fixed bug in vpowerspectrum that caused wrong indexOrigin of the output

lipsia (2.1.3)
  * fixed bug with wrong left/right orientation of the mni templates
  * the max number of threads is 4 unless the user does not set this parameter

 -- Lipsia Group (The official Lipsia developer group) <lipsia@cbs.mpg.de>  Tue, 02 Aug 2011 16:30:00 +0100

lipsia (2.1.2)

  * valign3d is now capable of multithreading
  * add uninstall target
  * interface of vswapdim changed
  * linked against libisiscore0_0.3.3
  * linked against libvia2_2.0.2
  
 -- Lipsia Group (The official Lipsia developer group) <lipsia@cbs.mpg.de>  Thu, 30 Jun 2011 16:30:00 +0100

lipsia (2.1.1)

  * isis dependent program are linked to libisiscore0.so.0.3.1
  * The bin size parameter in valign3d changed from 256 to 50 
  * Fixed some problems when working with huge images (>500 mb)

 -- Lipsia Group (The official Lipsia developer group) <lipsia@cbs.mpg.de>  Wed, 11 May 2011 16:30:00 +0100

lipsia (2.1.0)

  * Revised the REQUIREMENTS file
  * Fixed bug in vcheckdesign when showing powerspectrum
  * Fixed bug in valign3d. (saving a rigid transform as a vector deformationmap discards the rotation information)
  * New program: vnormdata. This program is a little wrapper script which performs a nonlinear normalization to
    a functional data set. Specifying an anatomical image will force vnormdata to use this one to find the transform to
    the reference image.
  * Revised the documentation
  * Renamed vtrialaver to vtrialaverage
  * Added niftov and vtonifti for backward-compatibility -> so we got Lipsia
    got the dependency to nifti again.

 -- Lipsia Group (The official Lipsia developer group) <lipsia@cbs.mpg.de>  Thu, 24 Feb 2011 14:10:14 +0100

lipsia (2.0.0)

  * New version of lipsia containing programs of the lipsia 1.6.1 and
    the last lipsia-sandbox version 0.4.3.
  * Old converters niftov, dictov, brutov, vtonifti are removed.
  * New version of vmovcorrection
  * Restructured documentation

 -- Lipsia Group (The official Lipsia developer group) <lipsia@cbs.mpg.de>  Fri, 05 Nov 2010 13:49:00 -0400

lipsia (1.6.1)

  * Fixed bug in vpreprocess (FreqFilter.c)
  * New version of vmovementcorrection written by PD Dr Gabriele Lohmann

